{"id": "EUVD-2022-54643", "enisaUuid": "910c01a2-3b51-3b04-9ba9-04bbb05d599e", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nigmp: Fix data-races around sysctl_igmp_qrv.\n\nWhile reading sysctl_igmp_qrv, it can be changed concurrently.\nThus, we need to add READ_ONCE() to its readers.\n\nThis test can be packed into a helper, so such changes will be in the\nfollow-up series after net is merged into net-next.\n\n  qrv ?: READ_ONCE(net->ipv4.sysctl_igmp_qrv);", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T02:23:23", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:36:53", "baseScore": 4.7, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9eeb3a7702998bdccbfcc37997b5dd9215b9a7f7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e20dd1b0e0ea15bee1e528536a0840dba972ca0e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b399ffafffba39f47b731b26a5da1dc0ffc4b3ad", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c721324afc589f8ea54bae04756b150aeaae5fa4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c2954671010cd1127d1ffa328c6e6f8e99930982", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8ebcc62c738f68688ee7c6fec2efe5bc6d3d7e60"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49589"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "053ade5a-4a25-393e-b252-633ebb6f756b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a9fe8e29945d56f35235a3a0fba99b4cf181d211 <b399ffafffba39f47b731b26a5da1dc0ffc4b3ad"}, {"id": "0994a3e5-93de-3145-94af-03df2cd313fb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.135"}, {"id": "3245a173-d6a2-3822-9fb4-32f68cec1f49", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.59"}, {"id": "37e7747e-c501-3688-818b-f1258c667444", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a9fe8e29945d56f35235a3a0fba99b4cf181d211 <9eeb3a7702998bdccbfcc37997b5dd9215b9a7f7"}, {"id": "50519208-116e-3452-b03e-a437cf807ba6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "56502b71-0629-31fa-80b0-005a9f6